<TITLE> Afghanistan suicide blast kills 10 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KANDAHAR, Afghanistan, Nov 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A suicide bomber detonated a vest packed with explosives in a crowded market in southern Afghanistan on Thursday, killing 10 civilians and wounding 13, a provincial police chief said. Uruzgan province police chief Juma Gul Himat said the bomber's vest exploded after he was fired on by troops while trying to attack a convoy of Afghan security forces. A media officer for NATO-led forces confirmed that 10 civilians had been reported killed in a suicide bomb strike in the area.
